  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Civil Society and Human Rights Organisation in Afghanistan (CSHRO)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CSHRO founded in 2004 by 25 civil society and human rights organisations. Today CSHRO is organised as a nationwide network consisting of 120 member organisations in 23 provinces, a Secretariat in Kabul and four regional centres with the technical support from the DIHR. 
The overall objective of CSHRO is to strengthen the further development of rights based civil society enabling it to promote the development of human rights; foster increased responsiveness of public authorities to the needs of people, increase the awareness of both the public authorities and of the citizens of public participation as a method of governance and of access to influence.</narrative>
  </description>
